com.inqwell.any.net

Class UntrustedCertificateException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • java.security.GeneralSecurityException
          • java.security.cert.CertificateException
            • com.inqwell.any.net.UntrustedCertificateException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class UntrustedCertificateException
extends CertificateException
    An exception that can be thrown by implementations of javax.net.ssl.X509TrustManager to indicate that a certificate chain is untrusted. The chain is carried in the exception and can be externalised as an Inq structure.

    An optional underlying exception can also be carried, if desired.

    Note: This is an unchecked exception. It can be used to pass control and data out of an X509TrustManager to a point where the checked exception declared by that interface, CertificateException, no longer appears (yet will pass through even if not caught, presumably by a similar exception tunneling technique).
